<subSubSection id="C358655E86066B20FA9B853BFA57F52C" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D586066B20FA9B853BFA57F52C" blockId="20.[1299,2281,2061,2743]" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686066B20F9C6853BF975F6ED" authorityName="Donald" authorityYear="1889" box="[1566,1775,2383,2422]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Stegocoelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786066B20F9C6853BF975F6ED" box="[1566,1775,2383,2422]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">Stegocoelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred from the Murchisonioidea to Loxonematoidea on the basis of the morphological similarity of the protoconch to Loxonematoidea. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686066B20F99085ACF890F59B" authorityName="Donald" authorityYear="1889" box="[1608,1802,2520,2560]" class="Gastropoda" family="Murchisoniidae" genus="Stegocoelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786066B20F99085ACF890F59B" box="[1608,1802,2520,2560]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">Stegocoelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a tall, smooth sinuated protoconch and dominant spiral cords on teleoconch without a distinct selenizone. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D5686066B20F7CB8641F772F5C0" authorityName="d'Archiac &amp; de Verneuil" authorityYear="1841" box="[2067,2280,2613,2651]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Murchisonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asparagales" pageId="20" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC786066B20F7CB8641F772F5C0" box="[2067,2280,2613,2651]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="83">Murchisonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to have a simple protoconch and a distinct selenizone.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
